                 <h2>Old foes reignite conflict in the league cup</h2>
                              <img src = "19.jpg" Width="500" Height="300" style="border:thick double #300000"/>

                              <p style="color:white;text-align:left">
                              
                              Swansea was the team that sent liverpool (then defending champions) out of the capital one cup two seasons ago right there at anfield, tomorrow liverpool would be looking to get a pound of flesh.
                            <br></br>  
   Though the team has been off form majority of the season and yet drawing a blank against Hull fans expectations and hope keep rising with each opponent the red army faces but so also is the teams spirit taking a down turn after each performance. Swansea are a team that's good on the ball and can hurt anyone, a side who loves to play free flowing football and high up the pitch which leaves spaces to be exploited behind the back four a pattern that's well suited to liverpool style of play which gives room for optimism, but liverpools approach should be more cautious this time around considering the teams lack of goals meaning there should be more cover for the defence line as less goals conceeded would boost confidence.
   <br></br> 
   A formation with two holding midfielders possibly a 4-2-3-1 should be a good option, this can quickly change into a 4-1-2-3 when trying to hit the swans on the break or 4-2-1-3 as the may suite the situation. Stevie needs to rest his legs as the capital one is an opportunity for younger ones to show they can step into the first team so Emre Can, Rossiter, markovich, Allen, and fit again almost forgotten suso  should all get game time finally its a good chance to see what Borini has to offer because balloteli slows down the teams attacks and often times looks lost in games.
   <br></br> 
   It promises to be a great match and with cautiously timed counter attacks liverpool should get this in the bag considering swansea aren't a physical side or a team attuned to playing aerial balls but that is not to say they cannot pull another one over the reds in this competition 'talk about lightening striking twice'

                              
                              </p>
                              

